result.execSummary:
Nicholas Harold Virgilito was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Nicholas Harold Virgilito was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
12:59 PM Defendant Nicholas Harold Virgilito in court.  Attorney Colleen Catherine Nordin in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Shannon Viel appears by video for Nicholas Virgilito. Court reviews hearing that took place on 10/19/22. Atty Viel indicates defendant is waiving his right and consents to extradition to the State of Colorado. Court orders defendant can be held up to 30 days without bail. Court schedules a review date  to check status of whether defendant has been picked up yet or not. 
Status conference scheduled for November 18, 2022 at 01:00 pm.

11:33 AM Defendant Nicholas Harold Virgilito in court.  Attorney Colleen Catherine Nordin in court for State of Wisconsin. Attorney Carrie LaPlant appeared by video for Nicholas Virgillito.  Court reviews events in file. Court reviews defendants rights. Atty LaPlant indicates defendant is contesting extradition, indicates had little time to discuss matter with defendant.  Court adjourns case to give SPD additional time to meet with defendant.
Extradition hearing scheduled for October 20, 2022 at 01:00 pm.
